# Header Readability & Typography Refinement

This plan addresses the "awful" readability of headers and labels identified in the visual audit. We will transition from high-intensity styling (all-caps, ultra-wide tracking, font-black) to a more balanced, professional typography system.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Daily Meeting View (Squad/All Mode)

#### [MODIFY] [DailyMeetingView.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx)

- **Personnel Assembly Header**:
  - Current: `font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-sm`
  - New: `font-bold text-base tracking-tight`
- **Sub-headers**:
  - Current: `text-[10px] font-bold italic`
  - New: `text-xs font-medium` (Remove italics)
- **Global Backlog / Active Sync Protocol Headers**:
  - Current: `text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em]`
  - New: `text-base font-bold tracking-tight`
- **Section Labels (Individual Tasks)**:
  - Current: `text-[11px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.15em]`
  - New: `text-[13px] font-bold`

